The '''[[Buru]] honeyeater''' ('''''Lichmera deningeri''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the [[honeyeater]] family. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Indonesia]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s and subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s.

